import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_datetime(data['actual'], errors='ignore')
    data['normal'] = pd.to_datetime(data['normal'], errors='ignore')
    
    plt.hist(data['actual'], alpha=0.5, label='Actual Temperature')
    plt.hist(data['normal'], alpha=0.5, label='Normal Temperature')
    
    plt.xlabel('Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of actual temperature compared to normal temperature?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], errors='ignore')
    data['normal'] = pd.to_datetime(data['normal'], errors='ignore')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_datetime(data['actual'], errors='ignore')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], errors='ignore')
    
    data['difference'] = data['actual'] - data['normal']
    
    plt.hist(data['difference'], bins=20)
    
    plt.xlabel('Difference between Actual and Normal Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the difference between actual temperature and normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
